is James Hogan's Thrice Upon a Time, which came out in 1980.

18:11.960 --> 18:15.700
But for some time, for a number of years, in fact, before I wrote Thrice Upon a Time,

18:15.740 --> 18:19.040
I'd been wanting to write a time travel book for a number of reasons.

18:19.900 --> 18:27.560
Firstly, I wanted to attempt to face up to the paradoxes, the logical paradoxes,

18:27.880 --> 18:36.800
once and for all, and answer them without top-outs, without convenient coincidences,

18:37.780 --> 18:43.860
and without obliging characters who just happen to do the right thing to make everything come out

18:43.860 --> 18:54.340
the way the author said. And secondly, I wanted to get away from this kind of cliche of some kind

18:54.340 --> 19:01.180
of a conjurer's box, described or described as whatever, that you jump into and you jump out of

